<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="306" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,487,765]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,631,656]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Comments:</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[404,452,632,656]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">type</typeStatus>
locality of this species is Campos do Jordão, in southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1189,1261,631,656]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. We now have additional material from two other localities in the Atlantic Forest. The original description and the redescriptions made by 
<bibRefCitation author="Vilela" box="[258,522,703,728]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" refString="Vilela, C. R. &amp; Bachli, G. (1990) Taxonomic studies on Neotropical species of seven genera of Drosophilidae (Diptera). Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 63, 1 - 332." type="journal article" year="1990">Vilela &amp; Bächli (1990)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Grimaldi" box="[581,894,703,728]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" refString="Grimaldi, D. A. &amp; Nguyen, T. (1999) Monograph on the spittlebug flies, genus Cladochaeta (Diptera: Drosophilidae: Cladochaetini). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 241, 1 - 326." type="journal article" year="1999">Grimaldi &amp; Nguyen (1999)</bibRefCitation>
are thorough and well illustrated. We add here photographs of of a malein several views. There is a discussion, ahead, about the 
<typeStatus box="[1070,1129,741,765]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">types</typeStatus>
of this species.
</paragraph>
